improved)', 'This is the dream come true app! Thank you!!! p.s. Would highly appreciate a dark theme.', 'Termux is life. Please make dark theme widget. Thank you very much.', "My bash scriptwon't work with it.", 'i want my refund. i downloaded this app but it is not installed in my phone..ðŸ˜¡ðŸ˜¡ðŸ˜¡ðŸ˜¡ðŸ˜¡ðŸ˜¡ðŸ˜ ðŸ˜¡ðŸ˜ ðŸ˜¡ðŸ˜ ðŸ˜¡', 'Dark theme', "Really love this, use it to run my scripts that control my media servers. One facility I'd like is to be able to suppress the 'script {name} executed' message. We have the 'termux-toast' feature, can output our own message, also 'termux-notify'. Great application all-round, recommended.", 'As a developer that loves his shell, this is fantastic. I can write, edit, and quickly run scripts on the go with a tap... well done.', "Bought it, didn't install with error 505. Can't refund it. Pity, termux \nitself is very useful.", 'Termux = "Simply-Amazing"', 'Just the perfect widget for a superb app!', "Love it. Let's me automate script running.", 'br', 'Best', 'I was expecting that using termux-dialog and termux-toast from API package together with widget would allow me to create useful actions and tiny apps without terminal running in foreground, however, terminal shows up each time I press a shortcut.. EDIT: An option to exit terminal immediately after execution (without pressing enter) would effectively solve this. EDIT: Support for background tasks is simple and works perfectly fine! Thanks Fred! 5/5', "If this app doesn't deserve support, I don't know what does.", 'Well worth the money to contribute to an open source project like this one.', 'Lovely lovely app.', "It's nonobvious that scripts need a weird hashbang path without documentation. Also needs a way to establish that a certain script should run in the background and not bring up an interactive terminal session.", 'Very handy, though it would be good if it closed the termux session after itself without me having to press enter', 'Very useful! Love it', 'Worth the money', 'Was hoping that it has some setting to allow me to run a shortcut in background (without switching to termux); but maybe I was asking too much'], 'appId': 'com.termux.widget', 'url': 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.termux.widget&hl=en&gl=us'}
